  "chapter": {
    "number": 13,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Burden against Babylon"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is the burden against Babylon that Isaiah son of Amoz received:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Raise a banner on a barren hilltop;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "call aloud to them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Wave your hand,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that they may enter the gates of the nobles.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have commanded My sanctified ones;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have even summoned My warriors",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to execute My wrath",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and exult in My triumph.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen, a tumult on the mountains,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like that of a great multitude!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Listen, an uproar among the kingdoms,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like nations gathered together!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The LORD of Hosts is mobilizing",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "an army for war.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They are coming from faraway lands,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the ends of the heavens—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD and the weapons of His wrath—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to destroy the whole country.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wail, for the Day of the LORD is near;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it will come as destruction from the Almighty.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2563
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore all hands will fall limp,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and every man’s heart will melt.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Terror, pain, and anguish will seize them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will writhe like a woman in labor.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will look at one another,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their faces flushed with fear.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, the Day of the LORD is coming—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "cruel, with fury and burning anger—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to make the earth a desolation",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to destroy the sinners within it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the stars of heaven and their constellations",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will not give their light.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The rising sun will be darkened,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the moon will not give its light.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will punish the world for its evil",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the wicked for their iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will end the haughtiness of the arrogant",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lay low the pride of the ruthless.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will make man scarcer than pure gold,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and mankind rarer than the gold of Ophir.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I will make the heavens tremble,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the earth will be shaken from its place",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "at the wrath of the LORD of Hosts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on the day of His burning anger.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like a hunted gazelle,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a sheep without a shepherd,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "each will return to his own people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "each will flee to his native land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whoever is caught will be stabbed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and whoever is captured will die by the sword.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their infants will be dashed to pieces",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "before their eyes,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "their houses will be looted,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their wives will be ravished.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, I will stir up against them the Medes,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who have no regard for silver",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and no desire for gold.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their bows will dash young men to pieces;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will have no mercy on the fruit of the womb;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will not look with pity on the children.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And Babylon, the jewel of the kingdoms,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the glory of the pride of the Chaldeans,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "will be overthrown by God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like Sodom and Gomorrah.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "She will never be inhabited",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or settled from generation to generation;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "no nomad will pitch his tent there,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no shepherd will rest his flock there.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But desert creatures will lie down there,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and howling creatures will fill her houses.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Ostriches",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2564
          },
          {
            "text": "will dwell there,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and wild goats will leap about.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hyenas will howl in her fortresses",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and jackals",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2565
          },
          {
            "text": "in her luxurious palaces.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Babylon’s time is at hand,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and her days will not be prolonged.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
